\section*{Structure of Class I MHC}
- Two polypeptide chains, a long $\alpha$ chain and a short $\beta$ chain, called $\beta 2$ microglobulin
- Four regions:
- Peptide-binding region - a groove formed from $\alpha 1$ and $\alpha 2$ domains of the $\alpha$ chain
