\section*{Summary of Aspects of MHC}
- MHC molecules are membrane-bound.
- Recognition by T cells requires cell-cell contact.
- Peptide from cytosol associates with class I MHC and is recognized by Tc cells.
- Peptide from vesicles associates with class II MHC and is recognized by Th cells.
